      {
        "contentUdi": "umb://element/77edc46528b443c5ac2c80fe1e9e0acf",
        "settingsUdi": "umb://element/15e2413e539b445782377313013d2a3c"
      }
    ]
  },
  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/af234782c6244e6ab06eeb11427b73bb",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Board role-playing games are improvisational theater, board game, and general story-making.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Therefore, a comfortable and exciting atmosphere depends not only on the master, but also on each player.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">In this article, we will give some recommendations on how to make your games cozier and more comfortable for the group.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/acaba2e2737f4c80958e4e8a67a3b60b",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Help from the master, and tips from other players may help a novice master, but don't go too far.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">There is one leader in the game, and even if you know the lore and rules perfectly, you should not take the reins of power from the master.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Remember the golden rule of all board role-playing games - the rules are not the main thing, the main thing is the fun of the game.</span></p>",
      "title": " Dispute with the master"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/a1a3d0a1a35f416ea7e7bb1f087e244f",
      "title": "Give time to other players",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Many players like to be the center of attention while playing their characters.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Some are so passionate about it that they try to fit into any scene, just because.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Remember that tabletop RPGs are a team experience, so don't take up other people's time.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">It's even worth encouraging the inclusion of other players in your scenes, such as asking a character for help.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/371376a2d9cc4c03b0e25645b112ced6",
      "title": "Act according to the logic of the game",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Don't rely on the excuse that this is what my character would do.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">If the whole party tries to sneak into the castle and one of the party betrays everyone to the guards, it breaks the story and the atmosphere.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/4ff109113db44f81846c82ac73634414",
      "title": "Separate the game and reality",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The characters in the game may have a conflict, but you should not transfer this conflict into real life.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Insults and finding out about relationships at the gaming table will not add pleasure to either the players or the host.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/78057544783b4a5bbea50c20f6a018d1",
      "title": "Accept defeat",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The task of the master and the group is to create an exciting story together.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Therefore, each defeat can give a new round of development as a character and the plot in general.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Complaining about the rules, complaining about the actions of other players and the master, manipulating the result of the throw, you put personal goals above the general comfort of the group members.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Remember, this is not a computer game, and here the character must always win.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/77edc46528b443c5ac2c80fe1e9e0acf",
      "title": "Communicate with the master and players.",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">If you have certain expectations from the game or some things are unacceptable to you, let the master know before the game.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">This is necessary in order for the presenter to make the situation during the game as comfortable as possible.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Enjoy your games and remember that there is nothing more boring than playing alone. Be responsible and friendly players!</span></p>"
    }
  ],
